    {
      "id": "ba1be571_163e627d",
      "file_path": "a1-policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/ccsdk/oran/a1policymanagementservice/controllers/v2/PolicyController.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 107,
      "message": "Does this mean that the returned value is an array? Because the Zalando rules specify that the top level data structure mus tbe a JSON object, contining an array if needed:\n\"Use JSON-encoded body payload for transferring structured data. The JSON payload must follow RFC 7159 using a JSON object as top-level data structure (if possible) to allow for future extension. This also applies to collection resources, where one naturally would assume an array.\" See: https://opensource.zalando.com/restful-api-guidelines/#data-formats\n\nThis question is relevant for all four occurences of responseContainer = \"List\" in this specification.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3763,
        "name": "Henrik Andersson",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "henrik.b.andersson@est.tech",
        "username": "elinuxhenrik"
      },
      "updated": "2020-08-18 07:07:50.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
